column2: An artist wants to choose which colours to use for his new painting. He places 9 different tubes of paint into a pag. He then picks out 4 different tubes out of the bag. How many different colour combinations can he choose?
A professional snooker player has placed 7 unique balls on the table. He is asked to pot 5 of the balls. How many different ways can he pot the 5 balls?
